| 2 | PII (emails) exposed without auth | 🔴 High | A02 |
| 3 | Missing security headers | 🟠 Medium | A05 |
| 4 | No rate limiting | 🟠 Medium | A04 |
| 5 | No input validation / body parsing | 🟠 Medium | A03 |
| 6 | Information disclosure in `/health` | 🟠 Medium | A05 |
| 7 | No CORS policy | 🟡 Low | A05 |
| 8 | Hardcoded data & port | 🟡 Low | A05 |

---

## Recommended Dependency Additions

```bash
npm install helmet express-rate-limit express-validator cors dotenv
npm install jsonwebtoken  # if using JWT auth
```

---

## Priority Action Items

1. **Immediately** add authentication middleware to all non-public routes — especially `/users`.
2. **Immediately** install and enable `helmet` for security headers.
3. **Short-term** add rate limiting and input validation before adding any write endpoints.
